    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Revival architectural style that is inspired by the 17th-century architecture of Belgium. Structures are typically large and made of rubbed red brick, sandstone, or limestone, often distinguished by incorporating a stepped gable.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
